Name of Library Service: Scenic Rim Regional Council Library Service
Address Line 1: Cnr Main Street and Yuulong Road

Notes:
Interlibrary Loans.

The Banana Shire Library Service offers a loan service for books not held in its own collections.
We can locate and request the item from another Library. There is a fee of $2.90 per interlibrary request, which is collected when the item is available for loan. Please be aware that we are subject to the conditions of the lending library, and if further charges are incurred, we will seek your permission before proceeding with the request.

Suggestions for purchase are encouraged for items that are current and popular.

View this library on Google Maps"

Our City Libraries Home Service calls monthly on those who are having difficulty accessing other branches of the library.

People of any age who are frail, disabled, or are carers can use our free personalised service on a permanent or temporary basis in their own home.

Retirement Villages, Pensioner Units and Special Care Hostels are visited on a monthly basis and folk enjoy being able to browse the shelves, discuss and recommend books. It becomes quite sociable.

Notes:
The City Libraries Neighbourhood Service provides a convenient service at many locations throughout Townsville. Think of it as a library branch on wheels!

You can join the library, reserve books, return books, use our internet service, or just pop in to browse.

The library visits Magnetic Island weekly, and travels as far south as Cungulla Beach and as far west as Woodstock. On Thursdays and Fridays the City Libraries Neighbourhood Service visits within Townsville's urban areas.
